# Claude Rules for Victor Uhnger Portfolio

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 + Designsystemet CSS
- **UI Components**: Designsystemet React (@digdir/designsystemet-react)
  - ONLY use Designsystemet components
  - NO custom components unless explicitly requested
  - Documentation: https://designsystemet.no/no
- **Animations**: Removed (not needed with Designsystemet)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Icons**: react-icons (only for icons not provided by Designsystemet)

## Design System - Designsystemet.no
- **Official Norwegian government design system**
- Uses CSS variables with `--ds-` prefix
- Built-in light/dark mode support via `data-color-scheme` attribute
- Components: Button, Link, Card, Heading, Paragraph, Switch, etc.
- Theme customization: https://theme.designsystemet.no/en

## Color Scheme (Designsystemet CSS variables)
Use Designsystemet's semantic color tokens:
- Accent colors: `var(--ds-color-accent-base-default)`, `var(--ds-color-accent-second-default)`
- Neutral colors: `var(--ds-color-neutral-background-default)`, `var(--ds-color-neutral-text-subtle)`
- Borders: `var(--ds-color-neutral-border-default)`, `var(--ds-color-neutral-border-subtle)`

## Design Principles
- Light theme by default with dark mode toggle
- Compact, bento-box card layout
- Minimalistic and clean
- Everything should fit on one screen (no unnecessary scrolling)
- Norwegian language for content
- Accessibility-first (WCAG compliant via Designsystemet)

## Development Workflow
1. ONLY use Designsystemet React components
2. Use Designsystemet CSS variables for colors (never custom colors)
3. Make git commits after completing features
4. Use Norwegian for UI text and labels
5. Keep components simple and focused

